That's supposed
to be a statistic.

00:24:14.970 --> 00:24:16.370
For us, it's not a statistic.

00:24:16.370 --> 00:24:18.575
We are much better
than this because I

00:24:18.575 --> 00:24:19.870
invest with my partner.

00:24:19.870 --> 00:24:23.915
And we would say we have one
company, which is in difficulty

00:24:23.915 --> 00:24:26.630
out of maybe 15 companies.

00:24:26.630 --> 00:24:29.610
But most of them, they
are in good shape.

00:24:29.610 --> 00:24:34.730
So I would say instinct of
the determination I have in--

00:24:34.730 --> 00:24:36.105
LINO CATTARUZZI:
In the founders.

00:24:36.105 --> 00:24:37.563
LOIC DE KERDREL:
--in the founders.

00:24:37.563 --> 00:24:39.570
I would say it's the first--

00:24:39.570 --> 00:24:43.222
it's my first key.

00:24:43.222 --> 00:24:44.930
LINO CATTARUZZI: And
the business itself.

00:24:44.930 --> 00:24:49.800
LOIC DE KERDREL: And of
course, the business,

00:24:49.800 --> 00:24:52.830
you need to be in a
market that is coming.

00:24:52.830 --> 00:24:54.980
I don't invest in where
there's no market,

00:24:54.980 --> 00:24:56.829
basically, where it's too soon.

00:24:56.829 --> 00:24:58.370
The time to market
is very important.

00:24:58.370 --> 00:25:00.730
For us, for example,
we were very lucky

00:25:00.730 --> 00:25:01.980
because of the time to market.

00:25:01.980 --> 00:25:02.645
It was not a strategy.

00:25:02.645 --> 00:25:03.740
It was luck, basically.

00:25:03.740 --> 00:25:06.350
But two years before,
we would have died.

00:25:06.350 --> 00:25:08.370
Two years after,
it was too late.

00:25:08.370 --> 00:25:12.990
So the time to market
is very, very important.

00:25:12.990 --> 00:25:14.810
But basically, the
profile of the founder

00:25:14.810 --> 00:25:19.516
is very important because
you have to adapt all time.

00:25:19.516 --> 00:25:24.320
If you have someone who is too
sure of where he wants to go,

00:25:24.320 --> 00:25:27.550
it's not good because you
need people who are very fast,

00:25:27.550 --> 00:25:30.800
who are ready to
change very fast,

00:25:30.800 --> 00:25:33.590
can adapt their business
model very fast.

00:25:33.590 --> 00:25:39.500
So I don't invest in people
who are too sure of themself,

00:25:39.500 --> 00:25:43.330
basically, because you
need to be humble, I guess,

00:25:43.330 --> 00:25:44.640
when you start a company.

00:25:50.630 --> 00:25:54.950
Yeah, it's part of
instinct, I would say first.

00:25:54.950 --> 00:25:56.970
And of course, I know a
bit of market as well.

00:25:56.970 --> 00:26:00.590
I invest many on
internet businesses.

00:26:00.590 --> 00:26:02.304
So I know--

00:26:02.304 --> 00:26:03.970
LINO CATTARUZZI: A
lot of the ecosystem.

00:26:03.970 --> 00:26:06.200
LOIC DE KERDREL: Few
things, few things-- and I

00:26:06.200 --> 00:26:12.070
try to invest not on a
single person or businesses.

00:26:12.070 --> 00:26:14.990
So I like to have at
least two partner.

00:26:14.990 --> 00:26:16.780
Three partner is good.

00:26:16.780 --> 00:26:20.190
I like a technical guy, a
business guy, and a design guy,

00:26:20.190 --> 00:26:20.690
for example.

00:26:20.690 --> 00:26:21.770
It's fantastic.

00:26:21.770 --> 00:26:25.880
That's the best
typology, I would say.

00:26:30.890 --> 00:26:33.000
I don't have my five
rules for investment.

00:26:33.000 --> 00:26:33.750
I don't have this.

00:26:38.240 --> 00:26:42.380
In five years, I
will have a good view

00:26:42.380 --> 00:26:44.090
if I am a good investor or not.

00:26:44.090 --> 00:26:47.500
For now, it's too soon.

00:26:47.500 --> 00:26:49.880
We had two companies
that was sold already.

00:26:49.880 --> 00:26:52.072
Good--

00:26:52.072 --> 00:26:53.280
LINO CATTARUZZI: Multipliers.

00:26:53.280 --> 00:26:54.860
LOIC DE KERDREL: Yes.

00:26:54.860 --> 00:27:00.030
And I'm still optimistic
in most of them.

00:27:00.030 --> 00:27:02.790
LINO CATTARUZZI: We'll bring
him back again in five years.

00:27:02.790 --> 00:27:03.957
And then he will tell us.

00:27:03.957 --> 00:27:05.040
LOIC DE KERDREL: Yes, yes.

00:27:05.040 --> 00:27:06.420
I would come.

00:27:06.420 --> 00:27:08.020
AUDIENCE: I have a question.

00:27:08.020 --> 00:27:12.250
So what are the main
difference between entrepreneur

00:27:12.250 --> 00:27:15.380
20 years ago and today in tech?

00:27:15.380 --> 00:27:17.492
And do you think the
same entrepreneur

00:27:17.492 --> 00:27:21.238
will have more chance of
success today or in the past?

00:27:21.238 --> 00:27:24.640
LOIC DE KERDREL: OK, well,
it's a good question.

00:27:24.640 --> 00:27:28.270
For me, it's much harder today
than 20 years ago because

00:27:28.270 --> 00:27:31.720
20 years ago, there
was a big, big thing.

00:27:31.720 --> 00:27:32.530
Internet was new.

00:27:32.530 --> 00:27:36.450
So this disruption was so huge.

00:27:36.450 --> 00:27:38.320
You don't find this
disruption today.

00:27:38.320 --> 00:27:42.170
I mean, so even someone stupid
would jump into the water

00:27:42.170 --> 00:27:44.590
and would follow the current
and would do something,

00:27:44.590 --> 00:27:46.115
I would say.

00:27:46.115 --> 00:27:46.990
It's a bit of a joke.

00:27:46.990 --> 00:27:48.955
But it's not totally a joke.

00:27:48.955 --> 00:27:54.530
If you were in the right moment,
now I find it very difficult.

00:27:54.530 --> 00:27:55.030
Why?

00:27:55.030 --> 00:27:58.330
Because all the smart
people going out

00:27:58.330 --> 00:28:00.790
of big university,
big business school,

00:28:00.790 --> 00:28:02.896
they all create companies.

00:28:02.896 --> 00:28:04.270
They all read the
same newspaper.

00:28:04.270 --> 00:28:08.322
LINO CATTARUZZI: Or
they work for Google.

00:28:08.322 --> 00:28:10.030
LOIC DE KERDREL: Or
they work for Google.

00:28:10.030 --> 00:28:11.830
It's true.

00:28:11.830 --> 00:28:16.360
I receive maybe 10
business plan every week--

00:28:16.360 --> 00:28:18.730
people who want to raise money.

00:28:18.730 --> 00:28:21.505
Quality of people is amazing.

00:28:21.505 --> 00:28:24.916
The business plan are fantastic.

00:28:24.916 --> 00:28:28.840
And so it's very
hard to find space.

00:28:28.840 --> 00:28:31.330
You have so many bright
people, smart people

00:28:31.330 --> 00:28:33.140
who create company today.

00:28:33.140 --> 00:28:35.470
I mean, I'm sure they will
not all success for sure.

00:28:35.470 --> 00:28:38.290
So I find it more difficult
now than 20 years ago

00:28:38.290 --> 00:28:40.290
because you have
much more people.

00:28:40.290 --> 00:28:42.670
And you don't have
such a big disruption.

00:28:42.670 --> 00:28:45.790
Maybe I was saying
to Lino, I would

00:28:45.790 --> 00:28:48.322
say abrupt change
is very interesting.

00:28:48.322 --> 00:28:49.280
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE] .

00:28:49.280 --> 00:28:51.154
LOIC DE KERDREL: Yeah,
abrupt change, for me,

00:28:51.154 --> 00:28:55.090
is probably the big disruption
in my opinion, in my opinion.

00:28:55.090 --> 00:28:58.840
But the other
disruption are extension

00:28:58.840 --> 00:29:03.097
of previous disruptions, I
would say, like mobile or video

00:29:03.097 --> 00:29:03.680
and all these.

00:29:03.680 --> 00:29:07.000
But big companies
are already there.

00:29:07.000 --> 00:29:08.910
You have to go.

00:29:08.910 --> 00:29:11.440
It's very nice when
you go in a market--

00:29:11.440 --> 00:29:14.110
not mature and a
bit chaotic, where

00:29:14.110 --> 00:29:16.730
big companies,
big organization--

00:29:16.730 --> 00:29:18.380
it's not easy for them to--

00:29:18.380 --> 00:29:21.370
so I would say blockchain is
perfect for this, I would say.

00:29:21.370 --> 00:29:23.318
AUDIENCE: Yeah,
actually, my husband

00:29:23.318 --> 00:29:24.779
was related to blockchain.

00:29:24.779 --> 00:29:27.015
What do you think
about the whole--

00:29:27.015 --> 00:29:28.470
people say it's a bubble.

00:29:28.470 --> 00:29:30.410
Some people say it's
a new technology.

00:29:30.410 --> 00:29:32.871
So what do you think about
the future of blockchain?

00:29:32.871 --> 00:29:36.190
LOIC DE KERDREL: Well,
people had the same idea

00:29:36.190 --> 00:29:38.650
with the internet.

00:29:38.650 --> 00:29:43.480
Very smart, educated people told
me that internet is a bubble.

00:29:43.480 --> 00:29:45.610
So I hear the same
with blockchain.

00:29:45.610 --> 00:29:46.300
So I think, wow.

00:29:46.300 --> 00:29:49.770
That's probably something good.

00:29:49.770 --> 00:29:53.440
And that's why I want to
dig in this direction.

00:29:53.440 --> 00:29:56.154
I think there is
something really--

00:29:56.154 --> 00:29:57.820
I don't understand
very well blockchain,

00:29:57.820 --> 00:29:58.850
to tell you the truth.

00:29:58.850 --> 00:30:01.090
I don't understand
everything in blockchain.

00:30:01.090 --> 00:30:05.140
But I feel that this is
something very, very disruptive

00:30:05.140 --> 00:30:07.220
that will change
a lot of things,

00:30:07.220 --> 00:30:10.310
like a new dimension of
business-- interesting,

00:30:10.310 --> 00:30:10.811
I think,

00:30:10.811 --> 00:30:11.726
AUDIENCE: Can I just--

00:30:11.726 --> 00:30:12.593
AUDIENCE: Sorry.

00:30:12.593 --> 00:30:14.757
This is more on a personal note.

00:30:14.757 --> 00:30:17.884
But do you remember if you had
a moment where you thought,

00:30:17.884 --> 00:30:19.330
OK, this is it.

00:30:19.330 --> 00:30:20.150
I've made it.

00:30:20.150 --> 00:30:22.670
I'm successful now, whether
it's founding a company

00:30:22.670 --> 00:30:24.000
or selling it.

00:30:24.000 --> 00:30:25.688
Or does it not work like that?

00:30:25.688 --> 00:30:27.400
LOIC DE KERDREL: No,
and I have a problem

00:30:27.400 --> 00:30:30.160
with the word "success."

00:30:30.160 --> 00:30:32.840
Success for me is
something really weird.

00:30:32.840 --> 00:30:35.080
I don't know if you have
read this in the newspaper.

00:30:35.080 --> 00:30:39.150
You have Albert Einstein.

00:30:39.150 --> 00:30:42.250
He wrote a note of paper
that was sold $1 million

00:30:42.250 --> 00:30:44.720
in an auction yesterday
or the day before.

00:30:44.720 --> 00:30:48.320
And it was a little word
on success and happiness.

00:30:48.320 --> 00:30:51.580
And he said
basically that he had

00:30:51.580 --> 00:30:55.780
found the secret of
happiness that it was not try

00:30:55.780 --> 00:30:59.190
to find success at all price.

00:30:59.190 --> 00:31:01.870
So success for me,
it's something--

00:31:01.870 --> 00:31:02.370
so we had--

00:31:04.960 --> 00:31:08.800
I don't really
feel I had success.

00:31:08.800 --> 00:31:11.870
For me, success is to achieve
your goal, and try to be happy.

00:31:11.870 --> 00:31:17.470
That's the only success you may
have in life, in my opinion.

00:31:17.470 --> 00:31:22.620
So if you are lucky
to make your business

00:31:22.620 --> 00:31:25.379
and to put it successful,
maybe develop it,

00:31:25.379 --> 00:31:27.320
sold it, make money.

00:31:27.320 --> 00:31:29.240
It's nice.

00:31:29.240 --> 00:31:32.246
So it's kind of a success.

00:31:32.246 --> 00:31:34.030
You have many little
success every day.

00:31:34.030 --> 00:31:39.085
So I never had the idea of
having made the success.

00:31:42.970 --> 00:31:48.250
For me, it was an obligation
to create my company

00:31:48.250 --> 00:31:50.410
because I hate orders.

00:31:50.410 --> 00:31:52.970
I don't like hierarchy
and this depends on it.

00:31:52.970 --> 00:31:54.466
So I had no choice, basically.

00:31:54.466 --> 00:31:57.359
[LAUGHTER]

00:31:57.359 --> 00:31:59.650
LOIC DE KERDREL: So that's
why I created a new company.

00:31:59.650 --> 00:32:01.340
So it was not a success.

00:32:01.340 --> 00:32:02.950
It was a survival thing.

00:32:02.950 --> 00:32:04.950
[LAUGHTER]

00:32:04.950 --> 00:32:08.554
LOIC DE KERDREL: So in a
way, I survived, in a way.

00:32:08.554 --> 00:32:09.970
LINO CATTARUZZI:
Oh, you did well.

00:32:09.970 --> 00:32:11.094
You survived well.

00:32:11.094 --> 00:32:13.760
LOIC DE KERDREL: No, my idea was
that we were lucky, very lucky.

00:32:13.760 --> 00:32:15.220
I was saying, we
were very lucky.

00:32:15.220 --> 00:32:16.320
It's not only luck.

00:32:16.320 --> 00:32:19.540
But we were very lucky
in all the stories.

00:32:19.540 --> 00:32:22.540
And I think I'm a
very lucky person.

00:32:22.540 --> 00:32:26.320
But luck is, of course, being
rapid in grabbing opportunities

00:32:26.320 --> 00:32:27.430
for sure.

00:32:27.430 --> 00:32:31.180
So I grab opportunities
if I can, of course.

00:32:31.180 --> 00:32:32.626
LINO CATTARUZZI: [INAUDIBLE].

00:32:32.626 --> 00:32:34.042
AUDIENCE: So your
company has been

00:32:34.042 --> 00:32:35.251
bought by the French "Poste."

00:32:35.251 --> 00:32:36.333
LOIC DE KERDREL: Yes, yes.

00:32:36.333 --> 00:32:39.150
AUDIENCE: So speaking about
change of culture and hierarchy

00:32:39.150 --> 00:32:42.179
from owning your company to
being CEO of a company, which

00:32:42.179 --> 00:32:43.470
has been bought by "La Poste"--

00:32:43.470 --> 00:32:44.410
LOIC DE KERDREL: Yes, yes.

00:32:44.410 --> 00:32:45.368
AUDIENCE: What do you--

00:32:45.368 --> 00:32:47.110
LOIC DE KERDREL: No, it's a--

00:32:47.110 --> 00:32:51.880
well, I negotiated, in the
deal, to keep my office

00:32:51.880 --> 00:32:52.870
far from the office.

00:32:52.870 --> 00:32:54.298
[LAUGHTER]

00:32:54.298 --> 00:32:58.300
LOIC DE KERDREL: And it
was part of the deal.

00:32:58.300 --> 00:32:59.234
They respected that.

00:32:59.234 --> 00:33:01.150
LINO CATTARUZZI: I worry
that they watch this.

00:33:01.150 --> 00:33:02.872
Or this is to
preserve the contract.

00:33:02.872 --> 00:33:04.556
LOIC DE KERDREL:
No, no, I'm very--

00:33:04.556 --> 00:33:08.120
and it's a big challenge
for companies to--

00:33:08.120 --> 00:33:10.350
"La Poste," for example,
they want to, of course,

00:33:10.350 --> 00:33:12.460
to have a digital
culture because they

00:33:12.460 --> 00:33:14.750
have a big problem.

00:33:14.750 --> 00:33:19.000
The stamps business, which is 20
billion euro turnover in France

00:33:19.000 --> 00:33:20.890
is decreasing 10% a year.

00:33:20.890 --> 00:33:21.520
Wow.

00:33:21.520 --> 00:33:22.400
What do you do?

00:33:22.400 --> 00:33:23.550
You have to find solutions.

00:33:23.550 --> 00:33:27.940
The strategy is to buy
companies, digital companies

00:33:27.940 --> 00:33:30.770
to prepare the future.

00:33:30.770 --> 00:33:32.330
But how do you do?

00:33:32.330 --> 00:33:33.400
They integrate that.

00:33:33.400 --> 00:33:37.220
They have not, in my opinion,
answered this question.

00:33:37.220 --> 00:33:43.927
And the fact that we're still
here, what's going to happen?

00:33:43.927 --> 00:33:45.010
When we're going to leave?

00:33:45.010 --> 00:33:47.080
Because the culture
is so different.

00:33:47.080 --> 00:33:49.840
And we fight to keep
our culture, basically.

00:33:49.840 --> 00:33:53.350
We fight to a certain
extent, basically.

00:33:53.350 --> 00:33:54.230
We fight.

00:33:54.230 --> 00:33:58.790
And we say, we think it's
a good idea to let us very,

00:33:58.790 --> 00:34:03.500
very far from you if you
want to keep the good people.

00:34:03.500 --> 00:34:05.920
They're going to leave if you
put too much hierarchy, too

00:34:05.920 --> 00:34:09.026
much of processes.

00:34:09.026 --> 00:34:11.150
LINO CATTARUZZI: But they
succeeded in this, right?

00:34:11.150 --> 00:34:13.219
You still could have
your own culture.

00:34:13.219 --> 00:34:13.635
LOIC DE KERDREL: They succeed.

00:34:13.635 --> 00:34:15.051
But it's a big
challenge for them.

00:34:15.051 --> 00:34:17.440
It's a big, big challenge
because I read something

00:34:17.440 --> 00:34:20.560
about the L'Oreal
CEO today, who said

00:34:20.560 --> 00:34:25.790
that digital culture come from
the ground, not from the top.

00:34:25.790 --> 00:34:28.760
You can't say, I want my group
to have a digital culture now.

00:34:28.760 --> 00:34:30.550
And you say, do it now.

00:34:30.550 --> 00:34:31.679
It doesn't work like this.

00:34:31.679 --> 00:34:35.429
It grows from the ground.

00:34:35.429 --> 00:34:37.790
So big challenge, I would say.

00:34:37.790 --> 00:34:39.300
But they're not too bad.

00:34:39.300 --> 00:34:43.362
They're not too
bad in doing this.

00:34:43.362 --> 00:34:46.793
LINO CATTARUZZI: Any
last questions, guys?

